div.p:

The ſixt was her wit, (ſeene in her cuſtome to peife or weigh her prey, before ſhee attempt to flie with it.) Rapta non protiaus ferans, ſed primè deponuns, (ſaith Plin
                     ••
                  ) expertaque pondus tum demùm abeunt: the manner of theſe birds is not to ſnach and away, but firſt to trie how heauie that is they ſeaze on, and if they finde it portable, then to bee gone with it.
